items.name: binomial-poisson-modeling
items.description: A project on categorical data analysis and discrete probability models using R. Includes café customer behavior observations, variable classification, and simulations with Binomial and Poisson distributions. Features parameter estimation, chi-square goodness-of-fit, and visualizations.

items.name: ml-lab1-salary-prediction
items.description: This repository contains Lab 01 of the Machine Learning course, focusing on predicting salaries using simple linear regression in R. It includes data exploration, correlation analysis, model building, and visualization of the relationship between years of experience and salary.

items.name: spam-detection-ml
items.description: A machine learning-based spam detection project using a synthetic dataset of email features. Implements data preprocessing, model training, and evaluation with metrics like accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score to classify emails as HAM or SPAM.

items.name: ml-preprocessing-vs-raw
items.description: This repository explores the impact of data preprocessing on regression modeling using the Carseats dataset. It compares models built with raw data versus preprocessed data, highlighting improvements through handling missing values, outliers, scaling, and encoding categorical features.

items.name: fit-and-residuals-emphasizes-model-fitting-and-diagnostics.
items.description: Exploring linear regression models in R using real (Carseats) and simulated data. This project covers predictor selection, multicollinearity, confidence intervals, and model diagnostics such as residual analysis and Cook’s distance. A hands-on dive into regression assumptions and insights.

items.name: naive-bayes-auto-mpg
items.description: This project analyzes the Auto dataset to predict vehicle fuel efficiency using machine learning techniques in R. Through data preprocessing, visualization, and feature selection, a Naïve Bayes classifier was trained to classify cars as high or low mileage, achieving ~88% accuracy with strong insights into key predictors.

items.name: lda-fuel-efficiency
items.description: This project applies Linear Discriminant Analysis (LDA) to the Auto dataset to classify cars into high and low fuel efficiency groups. It includes data preprocessing, exploratory analysis, model training, and evaluation, achieving ~88% accuracy in predicting fuel-efficient vehicles.

items.name: pca-knn-vs-classifiers
items.description: This repository contains R implementations of classification models including KNN, Logistic Regression, Decision Trees, and Naive Bayes. It explores the impact of Principal Component Analysis (PCA) on model performance using simulated data, comparing accuracy, sensitivity, specificity, and kappa statistics.

items.name: market-auto-logit-analysis
items.description: R-based analysis applying logistic regression to two datasets: Weekly Stock Market Returns and Auto MPG. Includes exploratory data analysis, model fitting, confusion matrices, and performance evaluation to assess predictive accuracy in financial and automotive contexts.

items.name: decision-trees-logreg-naivebayes
items.description: This repository contains implementations of Decision Tree, Logistic Regression, and Naïve Bayes models applied to the Iris and MTCars datasets. It explores classification and regression tasks, hyperparameter tuning, and performance evaluation using accuracy and RMSE, with visualizations for model interpretation.
